CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 5, 1956, pg. 30, reads: "Ammon Fencing Team - "En garde" and "Touche" are trade words used by the fencing team organized at Ammon Center. Top photo, front row, left to right: Lavell Russell, president; Clifton Mosley, James Robinson, Eugene Eggleston and Eugene Wilson, vice president.  Rear: James Murphy, Charles Betts, director; Wesley Moore, Marvin Godfrey, Charles Edwell, instructor, and Allan Keith...Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of boys' fencing team, front row from left: Lavell Russell, Clifton Mosley, James Robinson, Eugene Eggleston, Eugene Wilson; back row: James Murphy, director Charles Betts, Wesley Moore, Marvin Godfrey, instructor Charles Edwell, and Allan Keith, gathered on Ammon Recreation Center tennis court
